maml:description.maml:para: Copy a directory to a destination directory using ROBOCOPY.
Invoke ROBOCOPY to copy files, a wrapper.

One of the following operating procedures: 'MIR' ==> MIRror a directory tree (equivalent to /E plus /PURGE), delete dest files/dirs that no longer exist in source. 'COPY' ==> It will leave everything in destination, but will add new files fro source, usefull to merge 2 folders 'NOCOPY' ==> delete dest files/dirs that no longer exist in source. do not copy new, keep same. Default ==> MIRROR
Num threads in multi-threaded copies with n threads (default 8)
copy files in restartable mode.; if access denied use Backup mode. Requires Admin privileges to add user rights.
